The paper focuses on the application of reinforcement learning in the design and research of autonomous underwater vehicles (AUVs), which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep reinforcement learning and interactive RL also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The AUV's ability to adapt to a changing environment and learn from both human and environmental rewards suggests a potential focus on control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV) for environmental perception.
